FC Barcelona Database Project
This university project was created during my Introduction to Databases course. The objective was to design a small-scale relational database for a real organization — I chose FC Barcelona and focused on their financial operations.

Project Steps:

Defined the project goals and data structure

Built the schema using SQL and manually inserted sample data

Queried the database to extract insights on revenue, expenses, and key statistics

Created visualizations using Python (matplotlib) for clearer presentation

Prepared a summary presentation to explain findings

What’s Included:

docs/ – Concept note and context around FC Barcelona’s finances

sql/ – SQL scripts for schema creation, data insertion, and queries

visualizations/ – Jupyter Notebook with Python graphs

presentation/ – PowerPoint slides and speaking notes

Tools Used:

SQL (SQLite)

Python (matplotlib, Jupyter Notebook)

PowerPoint

